		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just wondering, I have searched a few sites. 
<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.google.com">www.google.com</a><!-- w -->
<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nesworld.com">www.nesworld.com</a><!-- w -->
<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nescity.com">www.nescity.com</a><!-- w --> (taken offline)
<br />
<br />But I was wanting to know if anyone had any technical advice or websites relating to creating multiple ROMs into ONE single Cartridge for the N.E.S. 
<br />I also wonder, If I download NES ROMs from a particular website, how could I copy the "code" into a particular cartridge and make the game play more than one game?
<br />
<br />Id like to add the fallowing:
<br />
<br />1. Faxanadu (English by HudsonSoft)
<br />2: Castlevania 1,2,&amp;3 (Capcom?)
<br />3: Excitebike
